# 10. Working principles (carry forward)

- Economic correctness is the hard part, not the HTML. The engine can be syntactically perfect and economically wrong.

- Two AI tools agreeing is not verification. Watch for an agent widening a test tolerance or using a wrong parameter — catch and revert.

- Keep agent context small and scoped (name the function, not 'fix the IS curve') to cut tokens and silent errors.

- File encoding repairs are one-shot verify-before-save; never PowerShell Set-Content on the HTML files.

- Adoption route: Frank using it in his own lectures beats any licensing deal. Build for 'a colleague asks for the file.'